# Docs - File naming conventions and structure
#
# docs/
# ├── architecture/
# │   ├── overview.md
# │   ├── system-design.md
# │   ├── data-flow.md
# │   └── decision-records/       # ADRs - ESSENTIAL
# │       ├── 001-choice-of-database.md
# │       ├── 002-authentication-strategy.md
# │       └── 003-microservices-vs-monolith.md
# ├── internal-apis/
# │   ├── service-a.md
# │   └── service-b.md
# ├── database/
# │   ├── schema.md
# │   ├── migrations.md
# │   └── queries.md
# ├── infrastructure/
# │   ├── ci-cd.md
# │   ├── monitoring.md
# │   └── logging.md
# └── onboarding/
#     ├── new-developers.md
#     └── codebase-tour.md
#
# The arrow character (→) is helpful.
#
# ### Common File Naming Conventions
#
# - Lowercase with hyphens: system-architecture.md, getting-started.md
# - Descriptive names: Avoid abbreviations; be explicit
# - Numbered ADRs: 001-decision-title.md, 002-next-decision.md
# - Index files: index.md or README.md in each directory for navigation
#
# ### Standard Top-Level Files
#
# Essential Files
# - index.md - Documentation landing page with navigation
# - ARCHITECTURE.md or architecture/overview.md - High-level system design
# - CONTRIBUTING.md - Often in root, but detailed guides in /docs/contributing/
# - DEVELOPMENT.md - Developer setup and workflow
#
# Common Additions
# - TESTING.md - Testing strategy and guidelines
# - DEPLOYMENT.md - Deployment procedures
# - SECURITY.md - Security considerations and practices
# - TROUBLESHOOTING.md - Common issues and solutions
